        "product_description": {
            "value": [
                {
                    "language_tag": "en_US",
                    "value": "ToolTreaux's butane pencil torch with adjustable and precise flame control is an essential tool to keep in your toolbox. The pencil torch is highly versatile, compact, portable, easy to use and refill, and will reach up to temperatures of 1300 degrees Celsius or 2370 degrees Fahrenheit.<br/><br/>Multipurpose hobby tools are always a valuable addition to your arsenal of craft supplies, and this butane torch absolutely fits that bill; the torch can be used for detail soldering, welding, jewelry design and repair, culinary, cooking or baking finishing and presentation, electrical work and lastly, will melt small brazing rods, glass tubing as well as many other metal materials like silver, gold and copper and more. <br/><br/>In addition to its versatility, the ToolTreaux butane torch is easily refillable using a standard butane lighter canister (sold separately). And, the butane torch or pencil torch features an aluminum body and brass control valve, neck and tip; these are durable, reliable materials that make this versatile tool able to stand up to lots of wear and tear and see you through a myriad of creative projects. <br/><br/>Package includes refill instructions.<br/><br/>Butane and refill canister NOT included with purchase.",
                    "marketplace_id": "ATVPDKIKX0DER"
                }
            ],
            "is_required": true,
